board.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/1/02 8:03:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1259.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legends Server</span><hr size=1> me and several others have said this before... and we keep saying it: <br>
<br>
You will never see any type of role playing utopia in any MMORPG game. Never. Period. <br>
<br>
By sheer design, MMORPG literally means massively multiplayer. That means every game server will always attract all sorts of people. From all over the freakin world. Different people. People who don't play the game the same way you do. And they never will. <br>
<br>
The only time that consistent role playing communities will ever be possible is when you play a game that is more limited in scope, less massive, less multiplayer. A game that allows the gamer community to take control (moderate) of their own game servers and to create their own house rules...... NeverwinterNights is possibly the first of these games. <br>
