I'm still going to see with my own eyes, but if it stinks, I leave. Also, I've seen that it does not even say RPing on it. What keeps Ubers from Ganging up on those Servers? Not a thing, back to the petition thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm the princess, okay?</span><br>  Posts: 495<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/1/02 8:53:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1259.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legends Server</span><hr size=1>    From the aspect of Firiona Vie -vs- Legends Server, all I can say is that if you expect to see more roleplaying taking place on Legends than FV, you are going to be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> sorely</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mistaken.<br>
<br>
   For the majority of EQ players (not FV populace, but the sum total of people who play this game), it's about meeting people online, makin a few friends, beating up monsters and/or working on tradeskills, and reaping the rewards.  The number of people who don't seriously roleplay <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> far</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> outweighs the number who do.  <br>
<br>
   If you take off the rose-colored glasses for a minute, you can see really damn clearly that the Legends servers are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> being designed with any intention of being a new home for die-hard roleplayers.  I mean, come on!  Find the first powerful artifact +3 and get it named after you?  Log onto your personal webpage and show off all the cool gear you have on you, and in the bank?  What the hell are you thinking?<br>
<br>
   I'm not saying the Legends servers wouldn't be fun.  If you like GM events, or collecting items, or fighting rare monsters, etc, I'm sure it'll be a blast.  I'm just saying that in no way, shape, or form, is that server <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> going to be chock full of level 60's with 100+ alternate advancement points who have pretty much maxed out on all the crazy gear their server has to offer and they thirst for more.  You won't even get the joy of starting out fresh, on an even playing field.  It'll be your FV character thrown into the mix, struggling to RP, amongst 2 year old shadowknights n such all screaming &quot;SOW PLZ!&quot; and &quot;ROFL OMFG BYOB Look at the Sword I just found it's named after me BADDA BING BABY!  HAHAHA!&quot;  Just log into your old server for a few and see how people act / talk.  <br>
<br>
   I'm not dissing other servers, or foaming at the mouth screaming &quot;Ubers -vs- RPers bla bla bla bla bla&quot;.  It's just that I've been on like 15 different servers, and I know what the others are all like, and I know what Firiona Vie is like, and if you're interested in role-playing, Firiona Vie is the best possible place to be.  I'm not even implying that &quot;being an uber&quot; and only playing the game for loot / xp is bad.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> It's not!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  It's just not my preferred playstyle, which is why you won't catch me touching legends with a 10 ft pole.<br>
<br>
Syllestrae Silverblade<br>
Warchanter of Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm the princess, okay?</span><br>  Posts: 496<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/1/02 8:57:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1259.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Legends Server</span><hr size=1>    Oh yeah, I remember that poll.  It was &quot;How much would you be willing to pay per month in order to play on a premium service server with more GM events n such?&quot;  and then had a bunch of prices listed, from 10 bucks up to 100 I think.  <br>
